{
  "texts": [
    "To select effective drugs, among the drugs that resulted in significant inhibition of bioluminescence signal (P < 0.05), we only selected drugs that resulted in 50% inhibition of bioluminescence signal as positive candidates.",
    "With this screen, we identified 42 drugs with therapeutic effects; seven acted on all three genotypes, and the rest only worked on specific genotypes (Fig. 7b, c and Supplementary Fig.",
    "We found that EGFR inhibitors Dacomitinib and Osimertinib inhibit LEGO growth in all genotypes, with a particularly strong effect on the PTN organoid (Fig. 7c, d and Supplementary Fig.",
    "7a), suggesting a strategy of patient enrollment for clinical trials for testing EGFR inhibitors.",
    "The Syk (spleen tyrosine kinase) inhibitor Fostamatinib inhibits all LEGOs, suggesting that Syk signaling is essential for GBM progression (Fig. 7c)."
  ]
}